The past three days, we've witnessed the celebration that Verve is- engaging events, insightful star talks and spectacular performances.

Until next year, bearing a promise of an even grander Verve, we remain the Literary Circle of NIT Durgapur.

caption.text:
After an overwhelming participation of young minds and their innovative ideas to various social challenges, it is time to celebrate the glorious moment. We, at ISTE NIT Durgapur, are thrilled to announce the winners of 'Technovate 2022'.
But first, we would like to extend our sincerest gratitude to the jury bench-- our respected professors, who could only choose the best entries of all.

It's not just the teams that won, here we all won-- society won with these innovations. So, we express equal heartfelt thanks to all other participating teams for being with us this long and making this event a success. We appreciate your creativity, time and effort behind your incredible submissions. It has not been easy for us to decide the winners, but tough decisions need to be taken. We are elated as we announce the winners from 3 domains each:

1.Healthcare:  Team Revivals
2.AI/ML: Team Free Thinkers
3.Smart vehicle: Team Sahanawaj

Heartiest congratulations to the winners!

Do follow our social media pages, so you don't miss out on any update on upcoming ones, till then think-citate-innovate!

#iste #hackathon #technovate #winners #think #citate #innovate #congratulations

caption.text:
The story of Easter is the story of Gods wonderful window of divine surprise.  Carl Knudsen 

And so, with Jesus' resurrection, Easter Sunday, also known as Resurrection Sunday, marks the power of forgiveness, the victory of good(rebirth) over evil(death), and that truth shall prevail.

It is that time of the year, when churches are decked up for a celebration again with vibrant floral decorations all around. But why do the brightly painted and chocolate-filled Easter eggs and, cute Easter bunnies being the star attractions then? Well, that comes from when common spring fertility rituals and summer elements being added to the religious concept to appeal to non-churchgoers in ancient times.

On this note, today ISTE NIT Durgapur, heartily wishes you all a happy Easter! May your wonderful Easter bucket be filled with hope, happiness and peace.

#easter #iste #easterbunnies #jesus #eastersunday #celebration #eastereggs #happiness

caption.text:
Hello Sir/Madam,
IEEE Student Branch NIT Durgapur is exhilarated to announce that as an institute of national importance, NIT Durgapur now has it's own online research portal dedicated solely to the purpose of establishing a convenient forum where aspiring researchers can directly connect to the personnel involved in ongoing research on the preferred topic, in a seamless manner. This portal also extends the scopes of research beyond the limits of the institute, enabling students from other colleges and universities to apply as well. The members of IEEE SB NIT Durgapur are overwhelmed to attain the realisation of this noble initiative which witnessed its inception back in 2020.

Poila/Pohela Boishakh is the first day of the Bengali calendar.This festival is celebrated on 14/15 April in the Indian states of West Bengal, Tripura, Jharkhand and Assam (Barak Valley) by Bengalis regardless of religious faith. This day has a huge significance and importance for Bengalis. Pohela Boishakh has been the traditional New Year festival in the state, with the new year referred to as the Noboborsho.(noboborsho means new year in Bengali).

So on this special occasion, Radio Nitroz- The official Radio Club of NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a very happy Poila Boishakh. Lets celebrate this Bengali new year with a diverse mindset and with lots of love.

As the season of internships and placements inches closer,  GNU/Linux Users' Group NIT Durgapur invites you to the System Design Workshop , a comprehensive session that will clear your fundamentals to tackle any kind of system design related queries.

caption.text:
Cultivation of mind should be the ultimate aim of human existence.

The chief architect of the Indian Constitution, Dr Bhimrao Ramji Ambedkar, was born on April 14, 1891 in Madhya Pradeshs Mhowand is fondly called Babasaheb by his followers to acknowledge his gratitude. Babasaheb, who belonged to the Mahar caste which was considered untouchable in Hinduism, converted to Buddhism after studying the religion for years on October 14, 1956, in Nagpur along with 500,000 supporters. After Independence, he was appointed as the law minister of India. We all feel by his journey from being an untouchable to the architect of the biggest constitution of the world. 

On that note, Radio Nitroz- The official Radio Club of NIT Durgapur, remembers and celebrates Dr B.R. Ambedkars birthday, and wishes everyone a very happy Ambedkar Jayanti.
